The pilot initiated a takeoff and, as the airplane became airborne, the canopy opened. The pilot 
attempted to close the canopy and lost control of the airplane. The airplane landed hard on the 
runway, which resulted in substantial damage to the airframe. The pilot stated that he failed to 
secure the canopy before takeoff and there were no preaccident mechanical malfunctions or 
failures that would have precluded normal operations.
The pilot's attempt to secure an open canopy during takeoff, which resulted in a loss of control 
and subsequent hard landing.
